ho played as an [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|Attacking midfielder]] in both Azerbaijan and Turkey.\n\n==Career==\n===Club===\nIn the summer of 2012, \u0130sayev left [[Gabala FC|Gabala]] to join [[AZAL PFC|AZAL]], six months later \u0130sayev left AZAL to join [[Denizlispor]] on a contract until the summer 2014.<ref>[http://www.trtspor.com.tr/Haber.aspx?id=43167.html Denizlispor transfere h\u0131z verdi ]{{dead link|date=October 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} {{in lang|tr}}</ref> In November 2013 \u0130sayev had his contract with Denizlispor terminated by mutual consent.<ref>{{cite web|title=Denizlispor iki futbolcuyla yollar\u0131n\u0131 ay\u0131rd\u0131|url=http://www.trtspor.com.tr/haber/futbol/ptt-1-lig/denizlispor-iki-futbolcuyla-yollarini-ayirdi-59034.html|website=trtspor.com.tr|publisher=Trtspor|accessdate=11 July 2014|language=Turkish}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{updated|match played 6 October 2013}}<ref name=\"NFT Stats\"/><ref>{{cite web|title=A.\u0130sayev|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/arif-isayev/88687/|website=soccerway.com|publisher=Soccerway|accessdate=21 December 2017}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|National Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Continental\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|valign=\"center\"|[[FK G\u00e4ncl\u00e4rbirliyi Sumqayit|G\u00e4ncl\u00e4rbirliyi Sumqayit]]\n|[[2006\u201307 Azerbaijan Top League|2006\u201307]]\n|[[Azerbaijan Premier League|Azerbaijan Top League]]\n|10||2|| || ||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||10||2\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\" valign=\"center\"|[[Simurq PIK|Simurq]]\n|[[2007\u201308 Azerbaijan Premier League|2007\u201308]]\n|rowspan=\"2\" valign=\"center\"|[[Azerbaijan Premier League]]\n|12||1|| || ||colspa