{"title_page": "Unilog Content Solutions", "text_new": "{{Orphan|date=November 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=September 2018}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Unilog Content Solutions\n| type = [[Privately held company|Private]]\n| genre = \n| logo = File:Unilog_logo.png\n| foundation = 1998\n| founder = Achutha Bachalli  <br /><small>(Chairman )</small>,CEO: Suchit Bachalli\n| dissolved = \n| location_city = [[Bangalore]]\n| location_country = [[India]]\n| location = \n| locations = \n| area_served = Worldwide\n| key_people = Suchit Bachalli <br /><small>(CEO)</small>\n| industry = [[E-commerce]]\n| products = [[Software]]\n| services = \n| revenue = \n| operating_income = \n| net_income = \n| aum = \n| assets = \n| equity = \n| owner = \n| num_employees = 600+\n| num_advisors = \n| parent = \n| divisions = \n| subsid = \n| homepage = [https://unilogcorp.com/ Official Website]\n| footnote = \n}}\n\n'''Unilog Content Solutions''' (or simply, '''Unilog''') is a global technology company specializing in [[e-commerce|eCommerce]] and product data management in the [[Business-to-business|B2B]] marketplace.<ref name=\"IRB2B\">{{cite news|last=Demery|first=Paul|url=https://www.digitalcommerce360.com/2015/01/12/unilog-plants-us-roots-grow-its-b2b-e-commerce-technology/|title=Unilog plants new U.S. roots to grow its B2B e-commerce technology|date=12 January 2015|newspaper=|accessdate=|url-status=live|publisher=Internet Retailer|location=|pages=|language=}}</ref><ref name=\"Crunch\">{{cite web|url=https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/unilog#/entity|title=Unilog|author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.-->|first=|date=|website=www.crunchbase.com|publisher=[[CrunchBase]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=}}</ref> Their flagship product is CIMM2, a software platform designed to facilitate commerce and communication between businesses.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pymnts.com/in-depth/2015/leveling-the-digital-playing-field-for-small-suppliers/|title=Leveling The Digital Playing Field For Small Suppliers|last=|first=|date=28 April 2015|website=PYMNTS.com|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The company is headquartered in [[Bangalore]], [[India]]<ref name=\"ET\">{{cite news|last=Khan|first=Sobia|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/services/retail/unilog-content-solutions-forays-into-luxury-retail-business/articleshow/31804729.cms|title=Unilog Content Solutions forays into luxury retail business|date=11 March 2014|newspaper=[[The Economic Times]]|accessdate=|url-status=live|publisher=|location=|pages=|language=}}</ref> with North American headquarters near [[Philadelphia]], [[Pennsylvania]].<ref name=\"Key\">{{cite news|last=Vider|first=Elise|url=https://www.keystoneedge.com/2015/06/25/in-wayne-unilog-grows-with-e-commerce/|title=In Wayne, Unilog grows with e-commerce|date=25 June 2015|newspaper=|accessdate=|url-status=live|publisher=Keystone Edge|location=|pages=|language=}}</ref> In 2015 and 2016, Unilog was named one of the \"50 Fastest Growing Tech Companies\" by ''The Silicon Review''<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://thesiliconreview.com/magazine/profile/50-fastest-growing-tech-companies-listing|title=50 Fastest Growing Tech Companies 2015|last=|first=|date=|website=The Silicon Review|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://thesiliconreview.com/magazine/profile/50-fastest-growing-tech-companies-2016|title=50 Fastest Growing Tech Companies 2016|last=|first=|date=|website=The Silicon Review|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> and has been positioned in the Magic Quadrant for Digital Commerce by Gartner since 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.enterprisetimes.co.uk/2019/11/19/unilog-releases-next-generation-digital-commerce-platform-cx1/|title=Unilog releases next-generation digital commerce platform: CX1 -|last=Edwards|first=Roy|date=11 November 2019|website=Enterprise Times|language=en-GB|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> \n\n==History==\nUnilog was founded in 1998 by Achutha Bachalli and Vatsal Poddar in Bangalore.<ref name=\"ET2\">{{cite news|last=Abrar|first=Peerzada|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/entrepreneurship/how-unilog-managed-to-change-fortunes-in-midst-of-slowdown/articleshow/17776457.cms|title=How Unilog managed to change fortunes in midst of slowdown|date=27 December 2012|newspaper=[[The Economic Times]]|accessdate=|url-status=live|publisher=|location=|pages=|language=}}</ref> The company was originally known as Srisoft and offered low-end B2B services like data entry and cataloging. Companies often outsourced engineering work to Unilog in its early days. In 2001, Unilog's employee base dipped from 100 to 15 as a result of the [[Dot-com bubble|dot-com bust]]. In 2004, Suchit Bachalli (the founder's son) joined the company. Also in 2004, Unilog earned its first major client in [[Fisher Scientific]], a [[United States]]-based [[biotechnology]] company.<ref name=\"Story\">{{cite news|last=Chamikutty|first=Preethi|url=|title=Age is no bar to startup, ask 70-year-old Achutha Bachalli of Unilog|date=29 March 2014|newspaper=|accessdate=|url-status=live|publisher=YourStory|location=|pages=|language=}}</ref>\n\nIn 2007, Unilog opened a [[research and development]] facility in [[Mysore]] where it now employs close to 600+ engineers. Two years later, the company began looking into potential product offerings rather than services.<ref name=\"Story\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/news/national/Unilog-sees-opportunities-in-Mysore/article20736554.ece|title=Unilog sees opportunities in Mysore|last=|first=|date=11 March 2014|website=The Hindu BusinessLine|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> In 2011, the business opened its North American headquarters in the Philadelphia suburb of [[Wayne, Pennsylvania]]. They also launched their B2B eCommerce software, CIMM2, that year.<ref name=\"Key\"/> One of the first clients to purchase and operate the CIMM2 software was SupplyForce.<ref name=\"IRSupply\">{{cite news|last=Demery|first=Paul|url=https://www.digitalcommerce360.com/2015/03/02/corporate-buyers-drive-online-sales-supplyforcecom/|title=Corporate buyers drive up online sales at SupplyForce.com|date=2 March 2015|newspaper=|accessdate=|url-status=live|publisher=Internet Retailer|location=|pages=|language=}}</ref> By 2015, the customer base in the United States had grown to around 100.<ref name=\"Key\"/>\n\nIn January 2015, it was announced that Unilog had been selected by the state of Pennsylvania to take part in the Keystone Innovation Zone tax credit program.<ref name=\"PBT\">{{cite news|last=Gough|first=Paul J.|url=http://www.bizjournals.com/pittsburgh/blog/morning-edition/2015/01/see-which-local-startups-are-getting-keystone.html|title=See which local startups are getting Keystone Innovation Zone tax credits|date=14 January 2015|newspaper=[[Pittsburgh Business Times]]|accessdate=|url-status=live|publisher=|location=|pages=|language=}}</ref> In September 2015, the company received an undisclosed amount of investor backing from Kalaari Capital.<ref name=\"VCC\">{{cite news|last=Sharma|first=Disha|url=http://www.vccircle.com/news/technology/2015/09/16/kalaari-backs-e-commerce-analytics-firm-unilog|title=Kalaari backs e-commerce analytics firm Unilog|date=16 September 2015|newspaper=|accessdate=|url-status=live|publisher=[[VCCircle]]|location=|pages=|language=}}</ref><ref name=\"Inc42\">{{cite news|last=Chandra|first=Nandini|url=http://inc42.com/flash-feed/kalaari-capital-invests-unilog/|title=Kalaari Capital Invests In B2B Ecommerce Startup Unilog|date=17 September 2015|newspaper=|accessdate=|url-status=live|publisher=Inc. 42 Magazine|location=|pages=|language=}}</ref> A month later, in October 2015, Affiliated Distributors (AD) announced that it would be deploying Unilog's CIMM2 software to manage its eCommerce offerings for its distributors.<ref name=\"IRAD\">{{cite news|last=Demery|first=Paul|url=https://www.digitalcommerce360.com/2015/10/07/distributors-collective-fires-new-digital-strategy/|title=A distributors\u2019 collective fires up a new digital strategy|date=7 October 2015|newspaper=|accessdate=|url-status=live|publisher=Internet Retailer|location=|pages=|language=}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2017, Suchit Bachalli was appointed Chief Executive Officer of Unilog and its global subsidiaries, succeeding his father, Achutha.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bizjournals.com/philadelphia/potmsearch/detail/submission/6417278/Suchit_Bachalli?l=&time=&ind=&type=&ro=0|title=People on the Move|last=|first=|date=|website=www.bizjournals.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nThe following year, Unilog began its partnership with independent hardlines distributor Orgill to make their eCommerce platform and product content subscription services available to Orgill\u2019s more than 6,000 hardware, home improvement, and building material retailers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hbsdealer.com/distributorsco-ops/orgill-adds-e-commerce-partner/|title=Orgill adds e-commerce partner|last=|first=|date=22 August 2018|website=HBS Dealer|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Products==\nUnilog's flagship product is the CIMM2 software system. It is an eCommerce platform specifically designed for businesses who sell to other businesses. It includes numerous features including a product information management (PIM) tool, product content management, an eCommerce shopping cart, multiple search and navigation tools, data analytics capabilities, and other features designed specifically to meet the needs of the wholesale distribution marketplace.<ref name=\"IRB2B\"/><ref name=\"IRAD\"/>\n\nThe company continues to build and evolve its product and service offerings and, in November 2019, announced the launch of its next-generation digital commerce platform, Unilog CX1\u2122<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.enterprisetimes.co.uk/2019/11/19/unilog-releases-next-generation-digital-commerce-platform-cx1/|title=Unilog releases next-generation digital commerce platform: CX1 -|last=Edwards|first=Roy|date=19 November 2019|website=Enterprise Times|language=en-GB|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>. The first module in the platform to be released, the CX1 PIM, was initially made available to AD members to give them the ability to manage product data and content for very large, complex catalogs.\n\n==Recognition and awards==\nIn 2015 and 2016, Unilog was named one of the \"50 Fastest Growing Tech Companies\" in the United States by ''The Silicon Review''.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":1\" /> Also in 2015, the ''[[Philadelphia Business Journal]]'' listed Unilog's North American President, Suchit Bachalli, among their 2015 \"40 Under 40\" list.<ref name=\"PBJ\">{{cite news|last=|first=|url=http://www.bizjournals.com/philadelphia/gallery/169611?s=image_gallery&img_no=6|title=PBJ announces 2015 40 Under 40 winners|date=31 March 2015|newspaper=[[Philadelphia Business Journal]]|accessdate=|url-status=live|publisher=|location=|pages=|language=}}</ref>\n\nUnilog has been positioned in Gartner\u2019s annual \"Magic Quadrant for Digital Commerce\" since 2016<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gartner.com/en/documents/3243418/magic-quadrant-for-digital-commerce|title=Magic Quadrant for Digital Commerce|last=|first=|date=2016|website=Gartner|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gartner.com/en/documents/3690217/magic-quadrant-for-digital-commerce|title=Magic Quadrant for Digital Commerce|last=|first=|date=2017|website=Gartner|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gartner.com/en/documents/3877477/magic-quadrant-for-digital-commerce|title=Magic Quadrant for Digital Commerce|last=|first=|date=2018|website=Gartner|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gartner.com/en/documents/3956505/magic-quadrant-for-digital-commerce|title=Magic Quadrant for Digital Commerce|last=|first=|date=2019|website=Gartner|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> and was cited in \"The Forrester Wave\u2122: B2B Commerce Suites, Q3 2018,\" evaluation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://go.forrester.com/blogs/a-just-published-forrester-wave-proves-that-b2b-commerce-suites-have-all-grown-up/|title=A Just-Published Forrester Wave\u2122 Proves That B2B Commerce Suites Have All Grown Up|last=Bruno|first=John|date=13 September 2018|website=Forrester|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Most recently, Unilog\u2019s software platform was selected as one of the top winners in The Software Report\u2019s \"The 25 Best Ecommerce Software of 2020\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thesoftwarereport.com/the-25-best-ecommerce-software-of-2020/|title=The 25 Best Ecommerce Software of 2020|last=|first=|date=|website=The Source Report|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> \u00a0\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://unilogcorp.com/ Official Website]\n\n[[Category:Companies established in 1998]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Bangalore]]\n", "text_old": "{{Orphan|date=November 2019}}\n\n{{Use mdy dates|date = April 2020}}\n{{Use American English|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Unilog Content Solutions\n| type = [[Privately held company|Private]]\n| genre = \n| logo = File:Unilog_logo.png\n| foundation = 1998\n| founder = Achutha Bachalli  <br /><small>(Chairman )</small>,CEO: Suchit Bachalli\n| dissolved = \n| location_city = [[Bangalore]]\n| location_country = [[India]]\n| location = \n| locations = \n| area_served = Worldwide\n| key_people = Suchit Bachalli <br /><small>(CEO)</small>\n| industry = [[E-commerce]]\n| products = [[Software]]\n| services = \n| revenue = \n| operating_income = \n| net_income = \n| aum = \n| assets = \n| equity = \n| owner = \n| num_employees = 600+\n| num_advisors = \n| parent = \n| divisions = \n| subsid = \n| homepage = [https://unilogcorp.com/ Official Website]\n| footnote = \n}}\n\n'''Unilog Content Solutions''' (or simply, '''Unilog''') is a global technology company specializing in [[e-commerce|eCommerce]] and product data management in the [[Business-to-business|B2B]] marketplace.<ref name=\"IRB2B\">{{cite news|last=Demery|first=Paul|url=https://www.digitalcommerce360.com/2015/01/12/unilog-plants-us-roots-grow-its-b2b-e-commerce-technology/|title=Unilog plants new U.S. roots to grow its B2B e-commerce technology|date=January 12, 2015|newspaper=|accessdate=|url-status=live|publisher=Internet Retailer|location=|pages=|language=}}</ref><ref name=\"Crunch\">{{cite web|url=https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/unilog#/entity|title=Unilog|author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.-->|first=|date=|website=www.crunchbase.com|publisher=[[CrunchBase]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=}}</ref> Their flagship product is CIMM2, a software platform designed to facilitate commerce and communication between businesses.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pymnts.com/in-depth/2015/leveling-the-digital-playing-field-for-small-suppliers/|title=Leveling The Digital Playing Field For Small Suppliers|last=|first=|date=April 28, 2015|website=PYMNTS.com|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The company is headquartered in [[Bangalore]], [[India]]<ref name=\"ET\">{{cite news|last=Khan|first=Sobia|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/services/retail/unilog-content-solutions-forays-into-luxury-retail-business/articleshow/31804729.cms|title=Unilog Content Solutions forays into luxury retail business|date=March 11, 2014|newspaper=[[The Economic Times]]|accessdate=|url-status=live|publisher=|location=|pages=|language=}}</ref> with North American headquarters near [[Philadelphia]], [[Pennsylvania]].<ref name=\"Key\">{{cite news|last=Vider|first=Elise|url=https://www.keystoneedge.com/2015/06/25/in-wayne-unilog-grows-with-e-commerce/|title=In Wayne, Unilog grows with e-commerce|date=June 25, 2015|newspaper=|accessdate=|url-status=live|publisher=Keystone Edge|location=|pages=|language=}}</ref> In 2015 and 2016, Unilog was named one of the \"50 Fastest Growing Tech Companies\" by ''The Silicon Review''<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://thesiliconreview.com/magazine/profile/50-fastest-growing-tech-companies-listing|title=50 Fastest Growing Tech Companies 2015|last=|first=|date=|website=The Silicon Review|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://thesiliconreview.com/magazine/profile/50-fastest-growing-tech-companies-2016|title=50 Fastest Growing Tech Companies 2016|last=|first=|date=|website=The Silicon Review|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> and has been positioned in the Magic Quadrant for Digital Commerce by Gartner since 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.enterprisetimes.co.uk/2019/11/19/unilog-releases-next-generation-digital-commerce-platform-cx1/|title=Unilog releases next-generation digital commerce platform: CX1 -|last=Edwards|first=Roy|date=November 11, 2019|website=Enterprise Times|language=en-GB|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> \n\n==History==\nUnilog was founded in 1998 by Achutha Bachalli and Vatsal Poddar in Bangalore.<ref name=\"ET2\">{{cite news|last=Abrar|first=Peerzada|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/entrepreneurship/how-unilog-managed-to-change-fortunes-in-midst-of-slowdown/articleshow/17776457.cms|title=How Unilog managed to change fortunes in midst of slowdown|date=December 27, 2012|newspaper=[[The Economic Times]]|accessdate=|url-status=live|publisher=|location=|pages=|language=}}</ref> The company was originally known as Srisoft and offered low-end B2B services like data entry and cataloging. Companies often outsourced engineering work to Unilog in its early days. In 2001, Unilog's employee base dipped from 100 to 15 as a result of the [[Dot-com bubble|dot-com bust]]. In 2004, Suchit Bachalli (the founder's son) joined the company. Also in 2004, Unilog earned its first major client in [[Fisher Scientific]], a [[United States]]-based [[biotechnology]] company.<ref name=\"Story\">{{cite news|last=Chamikutty|first=Preethi|url=|title=Age is no bar to startup, ask 70-year-old Achutha Bachalli of Unilog|date=March 29, 2014|newspaper=|accessdate=|url-status=live|publisher=YourStory|location=|pages=|language=}}</ref>\n\nIn 2007, Unilog opened a [[research and development]] facility in [[Mysore]] where it now employs close to 600+ engineers. Two years later, the company began looking into potential product offerings rather than services.<ref name=\"Story\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/news/national/Unilog-sees-opportunities-in-Mysore/article20736554.ece|title=Unilog sees opportunities in Mysore|last=|first=|date=March 11, 2014|website=The Hindu BusinessLine|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> In 2011, the business opened its North American headquarters in the Philadelphia suburb of [[Wayne, Pennsylvania]]. They also launched their B2B eCommerce software, CIMM2, that year.<ref name=\"Key\"/> One of the first clients to purchase and operate the CIMM2 software was SupplyForce.<ref name=\"IRSupply\">{{cite news|last=Demery|first=Paul|url=https://www.digitalcommerce360.com/2015/03/02/corporate-buyers-drive-online-sales-supplyforcecom/|title=Corporate buyers drive up online sales at SupplyForce.com|date=March 2, 2015|newspaper=|accessdate=|url-status=live|publisher=Internet Retailer|location=|pages=|language=}}</ref> By 2015, the customer base in the United States had grown to around 100.<ref name=\"Key\"/>\n\nIn January 2015, it was announced that Unilog had been selected by the state of Pennsylvania to take part in the Keystone Innovation Zone tax credit program.<ref name=\"PBT\">{{cite news|last=Gough|first=Paul J.|url=http://www.bizjournals.com/pittsburgh/blog/morning-edition/2015/01/see-which-local-startups-are-getting-keystone.html|title=See which local startups are getting Keystone Innovation Zone tax credits|date=January 14, 2015|newspaper=[[Pittsburgh Business Times]]|accessdate=|url-status=live|publisher=|location=|pages=|language=}}</ref> In September 2015, the company received an undisclosed amount of investor backing from Kalaari Capital.<ref name=\"VCC\">{{cite news|last=Sharma|first=Disha|url=http://www.vccircle.com/news/technology/2015/09/16/kalaari-backs-e-commerce-analytics-firm-unilog|title=Kalaari backs e-commerce analytics firm Unilog|date=September 16, 2015|newspaper=|accessdate=|url-status=live|publisher=[[VCCircle]]|location=|pages=|language=}}</ref><ref name=\"Inc42\">{{cite news|last=Chandra|first=Nandini|url=http://inc42.com/flash-feed/kalaari-capital-invests-unilog/|title=Kalaari Capital Invests In B2B Ecommerce Startup Unilog|date=September 17, 2015|newspaper=|accessdate=|url-status=live|publisher=Inc. 42 Magazine|location=|pages=|language=}}</ref> A month later, in October 2015, Affiliated Distributors (AD) announced that it would be deploying Unilog's CIMM2 software to manage its eCommerce offerings for its distributors.<ref name=\"IRAD\">{{cite news|last=Demery|first=Paul|url=https://www.digitalcommerce360.com/2015/10/07/distributors-collective-fires-new-digital-strategy/|title=A distributors\u2019 collective fires up a new digital strategy|date=October 7, 2015|newspaper=|accessdate=|url-status=live|publisher=Internet Retailer|location=|pages=|language=}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2017, Suchit Bachalli was appointed Chief Executive Officer of Unilog and its global subsidiaries, succeeding his father, Achutha.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bizjournals.com/philadelphia/potmsearch/detail/submission/6417278/Suchit_Bachalli?l=&time=&ind=&type=&ro=0|title=People on the Move|last=|first=|date=|website=www.bizjournals.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nThe following year, Unilog began its partnership with independent hardlines distributor Orgill to make their eCommerce platform and product content subscription services available to Orgill\u2019s more than 6,000 hardware, home improvement, and building material retailers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hbsdealer.com/distributorsco-ops/orgill-adds-e-commerce-partner/|title=Orgill adds e-commerce partner|last=|first=|date=August 22, 2018|website=HBS Dealer|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Products==\nUnilog's flagship product is the CIMM2 software system. It is an eCommerce platform specifically designed for businesses who sell to other businesses. It includes numerous features including a product information management (PIM) tool, product content management, an eCommerce shopping cart, multiple search and navigation tools, data analytics capabilities, and other features designed specifically to meet the needs of the wholesale distribution marketplace.<ref name=\"IRB2B\"/><ref name=\"IRAD\"/>\n\nThe company continues to build and evolve its product and service offerings and, in November 2019, announced the launch of its next-generation digital commerce platform, Unilog CX1\u2122<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.enterprisetimes.co.uk/2019/11/19/unilog-releases-next-generation-digital-commerce-platform-cx1/|title=Unilog releases next-generation digital commerce platform: CX1 -|last=Edwards|first=Roy|date=November 19, 2019|website=Enterprise Times|language=en-GB|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>. The first module in the platform to be released, the CX1 PIM, was initially made available to AD members to give them the ability to manage product data and content for very large, complex catalogs.\n\n==Recognition and awards==\nIn 2015 and 2016, Unilog was named one of the \"50 Fastest Growing Tech Companies\" in the United States by ''The Silicon Review''.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":1\" /> Also in 2015, the ''[[Philadelphia Business Journal]]'' listed Unilog's North American President, Suchit Bachalli, among their 2015 \"40 Under 40\" list.<ref name=\"PBJ\">{{cite news|last=|first=|url=http://www.bizjournals.com/philadelphia/gallery/169611?s=image_gallery&img_no=6|title=PBJ announces 2015 40 Under 40 winners|date=March 31, 2015|newspaper=[[Philadelphia Business Journal]]|accessdate=|url-status=live|publisher=|location=|pages=|language=}}</ref>\n\nUnilog has been positioned in Gartner\u2019s annual \u201cMagic Quadrant for Digital Commerce\u201d since 2016<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gartner.com/en/documents/3243418/magic-quadrant-for-digital-commerce|title=Magic Quadrant for Digital Commerce|last=|first=|date=2016|website=Gartner|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gartner.com/en/documents/3690217/magic-quadrant-for-digital-commerce|title=Magic Quadrant for Digital Commerce|last=|first=|date=2017|website=Gartner|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gartner.com/en/documents/3877477/magic-quadrant-for-digital-commerce|title=Magic Quadrant for Digital Commerce|last=|first=|date=2018|website=Gartner|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gartner.com/en/documents/3956505/magic-quadrant-for-digital-commerce|title=Magic Quadrant for Digital Commerce|last=|first=|date=2019|website=Gartner|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> and was cited in \u201cThe Forrester Wave\u2122: B2B Commerce Suites, Q3 2018,\u201d evaluation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://go.forrester.com/blogs/a-just-published-forrester-wave-proves-that-b2b-commerce-suites-have-all-grown-up/|title=A Just-Published Forrester Wave\u2122 Proves That B2B Commerce Suites Have All Grown Up|last=Bruno|first=John|date=September 13, 2018|website=Forrester|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Most recently, Unilog\u2019s software platform was selected as one of the top winners in The Software Report\u2019s \u201cThe 25 Best Ecommerce Software of 2020\u201d.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thesoftwarereport.com/the-25-best-ecommerce-software-of-2020/|title=The 25 Best Ecommerce Software of 2020|last=|first=|date=|website=The Source Report|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> \u00a0\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://unilogcorp.com/ Official Website]\n\n[[Category:Companies established in 1998]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Bangalore]]\n", "name_user": "Dl2000", "label": "safe", "comment": "repair template damage; tidy", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unilog_Content_Solutions"}
